<br>
At the time, we had one account and one computer.  Realizing that we were both really enjoying the game, we bought a second account.  John kept his enchanter and I started a new shaman on the second account.<br>
<br>
In March of 2000, we bought a second computer and started grouping together.  We had a really good time and fell in with a regular group of friends and played nearly every night.  I can't imagine playing EQ with John and NOT grouping together (exp not raiding).  We joined the same guild.<br>
<br>
Late last summer, John managed to kick the EQ habit and retired his 57 enchanter, Ving.  We're both very computer oriented people and our computers are still side by side, so we still spend a lot of time together doing different things on the computer.  <br>
<br>
The good thing is, he understands the game and the addiction.  I don't think I could play EQ as much as I do if my significant other didn't &quot;get&quot; EQ: the lack of a pause button, the fact that others are depending on you in game, the lingo, the stories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kidin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/31/02 9:07:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10255.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ and a happy marriage</span><hr size=1> Hail,<br>
<br>
It took me a LONG time to convince my spouse to play.<br>
Watched over my shoulder, but couldn't really &quot;get&quot; the game for some time.<br>
<br>
Finally the hook sank in, and we play regularly together (and separately) almost every day now.  Getting the second account took much longer for us, but it did happen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We paid for a character transfer rather than one of us start again.  We're both rather attached to our primary characters.<br>
<br>
(Rather funny, Glori, we're an Ench/Shaman combo as well!)<br>
<br>
Before we both played, Everquest was a slight strain on our marriage.  Missed family dinners, late night CR's causing lack of sleep and thus a shorter fuse on my temper and increased irritability the following day, etc.<br>
<br>
Since we both play now, it adds to the time we spend together, which I think is a good thing, although the game still interferes sometimes with our other plans if we let it.<br>
<br>
The game is what you make of it.<br>
A marriage is also, although magnified by a large factor. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
